<TITLE> Senior Management -- Heritage </TITLE>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/heritage/thf_log2.gif" width=334 height=104 border=0 alt="Heritage Foundation logo graphic">
<BR>
<H3>SENIOR MANAGEMENT</H3></CENTER>
<HR SIZE=2 WIDTH=30%>
<DL>

<DT><A HREF="/heritage/staff/feulner.html">Dr. Edwin J. Feulner, Jr.</A>, <I>President</I> 
<DD>Past Chairman, Intercollegiate Studies
Institute; Executive  Committee, Council for National Policy; Treasurer, Mont 
Pelerin Society; Past President,  Philadelphia Society; Member, U.S. Advisory 
Commission on Public Diplomacy, Chairman 1982-91;  Member, Clare Boothe Luce 
Fund; Former Director, House Republican Study Committee. B.S.,  Regis College; 
M.B.A., University of Pennsylvania's Wharton School; Ph.D., University of Edinburgh.
<P>
<DT><A HREF="/heritage/staff/truluck.htm">Phillip N. Truluck</A>, <I>Executive Vice President</I> 
<DD>Public Member, Administrative Conference of the  United States; Founding Director, Center for International 
Private Enterprise; Member, President's  Private Sector Survey on Cost Control 
(Grace Commission); Former Deputy Director, Republican  Study Committee. B.S., 
University of South Carolina.
<P>
<DT><a href="/heritage/staff/blatz.html">Robert G. Blatz</a>, <i>Vice President, Administration and Chief Financial Officer</i>
<DD>Former chief of staff, Heritage President Edwin Feulner; previously, Company Commander, U.S. Army; recipient of  MacArthur Leadership Award and the Meritorious Service Medal for outstanding achievement. B.A., U.S. Military Academy at West Point, pursuing masters' degrees in legislative affairs and business administration, George Washington University.
<p>    
<DT>Herb M. Berkowitz, <i>Vice President, Public Relations</i>
<DD>Named one of the public relations industry's top 100 "superstars" by Public Relations Quarterly; recipient of Public Relations Society of America's Silver Anvil Award, 1985; Former Associate Editor, Armed Forces Journal. B.A., George Washington University. 
<p>
<DT><A HREF="/heritage/staff/butler.htm">Dr. Stuart M. Butler</A>, <I>Vice President and Director, Domestic Policy Studies; 
Director, Roe Institute  for Economic Policy Studies</I>
<DD>Co-author, "Out of the Poverty Trap: A Conservative Strategy for  Welfare Reform"; co-author, Heritage Consumer Choice Health Plan; author, "Enterprise Zones:  Greenlining the Inner 
Cities" and "Privatizing Federal Spending." B.Sc., M.A., Ph.D., St. Andrews  University.
<p>
<DT><a href="/heritage/staff/gaynerl.htm">Lewis F. Gayner</a>, <i>Vice President, External Relations</i> 
<dd>Former long-time Dow Chemical executive who spearheads Heritage outreach to the business community, other policy organizations, and the nation's governors. M.A., Stanford University. 

<P>
<DT><A HREF="/heritage/staff/holmes.htm">Dr. Kim R. Holmes</A>, <I>Vice President and Director, Foreign Policy and Defense 
Studies</I> 
<DD>Editor, "A  Safe and Prosperous America: A U.S. Foreign and Defense 
Policy Blueprint", and Co- editor,  "Reshaping Europe: Strategies for a Post-Cold 
War Europe." Former Senior Fellow, Institute for  Foreign Policy Analysis in 
association with Tufts University. B.A., University of Florida; Ph.D. and  
M.A., Georgetown University.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="/heritage/staff/meyerson.htm">Adam Meyerson</A>, <I>Vice President, Educational Affairs and Editor, Policy Review: The Journal of American Citizenship</I>
<DD>Member of the  Board, American Institute of Public Service; former Editorial 
Writer, The Wall Street Journal;  Co-editor, "The Wall Street Journal on Management"; 
previously Managing Editor, The American  Spectator. B.A., Yale University.

<P>
 
<DT><A HREF="/heritage/staff/vonkan.htm">John Von Kannon</A>, <I>Vice President and Treasurer</I>  
<DD>Publisher, Heritage Member News and The  Windsor Newsletter. Former President, Russell & Von Kannon; previously Publisher, <i>The American  Spectator</i>. B.A., Indiana University. 

<P>
<DT><a href="/heritage/staff/arnett.html">Grace-Marie Arnett</a>, <I>Vice President, Information Marketing</i>
<dd>Founder, Arnett & Co., public policy consulting firm; former Executive Director, <a href="http://www.townhall.com/taxcom">National Commission on Economic Growth
and Tax Reform</a>; previously,  senior policy advisor to the Forbes for
President campaign. B.A., University of New Mexico.  
<p> 

<P>
